  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;The proposed rear extension, by reason of its excessive height and depth would create a detrimental impact against the occupiers of the adjoining property at No.152 in terms of loss of daylight/sunlight by virtue of overshadowing a rear facing window which serves a habitable room to their property, and general loss of outlook and an increase sense of enclosure and tunneling effect.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;Reason: The proposed development falls contrary to&amp;nbsp;policies LP1 and LP2&amp;nbsp;of the LP33 Hackney Local Plan 2020 and Policies 3.5 and 7.6 of the London Plan 2016 (as amended) and guidance&amp;nbsp;contained within Hackney Council’s SPD on ‘Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document’ 2009 and ’NPPF’ 2019 (as amended).&lt;/p&gt;"
